tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All measured parameters are within or close to normal limits, except for mildly elevated potassium and chloride. Renal function, glucose metabolism, and lipid profile are unremarkable. The slight hyperkalemia and hyperchloremia may warrant repeat testing and clinical correlation, but no acute laboratory abnormalities are evident. Overall, results are stable and reassuring.
